msgid ""
"`ptool.run(options)` is also supported, where `options` is a table with the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:547
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:547"
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:548
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:548"
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:549
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:549"
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): The child process working directory."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:550
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:550"
msgid ""
"`env` (table, optional): Additional environment variables, where keys are "
"variable names and values are variable values."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:552
msgid ""
"`stdin` (string, optional): String sent to the child process stdin. When "
"this is omitted, the child process inherits the current process stdin."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:554
msgid ""
"`trim` (boolean, optional): Whether to trim leading and trailing whitespace "
"from captured `stdout` and captured `stderr` before returning them. This "
"only affects streams set to `\"capture\"`. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid ""
"`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information for this "
"execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })"
"` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `true`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:560
msgid ""
"`check` (boolean, optional): Whether to raise an error immediately when the "
"exit code is not `0`. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { check = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is "
"`false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:563
msgid ""
"`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation "
"before execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default "
"is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:566
msgid ""
"`retry` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user whether to retry after "
"a failed execution when `check = true`. If omitted, the value from "
"`ptool.config({ run = { retry = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, "
"the default is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:570
msgid ""
"`stdout` (string, optional): Stdout handling strategy. Supported values:"
msgstr ""

