#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:705
msgid ""
"`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information before "
"replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { echo = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is "
"`true`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:708
msgid ""
"`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation "
"before replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default "
"is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:711
msgid ""
"Unlike `ptool.run`, `ptool.exec` does not support `stdin`, `trim`, `stdout`, "
"`stderr`, `check`, or `retry`."
msgstr ""

